description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 4 Support Worker to join our Crisis Resolution and Home treatment team in Eastbourne.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting new opportunity that we believe will add real value to our services. We are aiming to provide a smother transition from inpatient to community care, create more opportunities for early discharge from hospital, focused crisis and relapse prevention planning and this post will be instrumental in this development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will form part of an additional resource allocated specifically to achieve the above goals and improve crisis intervention work overall. You will be working with people when they first present to Crisis Home Treatment Team until the point of discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be a challenging but rewarding role, working with people presenting with a range of mental health issues and risks. You will need to demonstrate how you can work in a fast paced environment, have the ability to be dynamic and adaptable and also be able manage you own stress and resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful postholder will work within a dedicated, dynamic and enthusiastic team, and will receive appropriate support and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynn Huggins, Team Leader, on 01323 438279.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
